Close friends of Samburu West MP Naisula Lesuuda visited her recently, bearing gifts for her newborn. The politician is currently on maternity leave after she welcomed her firstborn child. Her visitors brought her many expensive and thoughtful gifts for her baby, and she was overwhelmed with love. "Feeling the love," Lesuuda wrote on social media. Lesuuda posted on Instagram, thanking the friends for their kindness. Revealing the name of her child, she wrote, "Melau, indeed you will never lack love from your uncles and aunties." She also showed off her girl squad. Describing it as,Â "Friends that become family."